# HexStrike-AI CTF Evaluation — Prompt Folder

## What this is
Pre-built prompt sequences for running HexStrike-AI evaluation experiments across PicoCTF challenges.
529 exercises total: 88 challenges × 3 clients × 2 LLMs.

## Folder structure
```
LLM/
└── Client/
    └── Category/
        └── Difficulty/
            └── Exercise/
                └── Files/
```
**Example:** `Claude/Claude/Web/Easy/Cookies/Files/`

## Prompt structure
Each exercise file contains two prompts sent in order:

**Prompt 1** — Initializes the HexStrike session. Do not modify.

**Prompt 2** — Contains 3 experiment variants. Pick one per run and send it as-is, followed by the exercise block below it.

The exercise block at the bottom of each file contains the challenge name, description, and a Results section to fill in after each run.

## Before running

**[PORT]** — If the exercise contains `[PORT]`, replace it with the actual port from the PicoCTF challenge panel before sending.

**Instance** — Some exercises require launching an instance on PicoCTF before connecting. Check the challenge page. No instance info is written in the prompt files themselves.

**Files** — Some exercises require attaching a file to Prompt 2. All required files are pre-downloaded in the `Files/` folder inside each exercise directory. Attach as needed.

**Nothing extra** — Some exercises require none of the above. Just send the prompts.

## Experiment variants
| Variant | Description |
|---|---|
| Experiment 1 | Free solve — any tools, any method |
| Experiment 2 | HexStrike tools only, ranked |
| Experiment 3 | HexStrike tools only, no outside logic, strict adherence |